property_description:
This historic home, directly on Main Street in downtown Reisterstown, has been renovated for office space. It has road frontage with high traffic volume. Classic wood floors and fire places. Private front door entry area for both upstairs and downstairs offices. 

The first floor entry has a reception area with fireplace, 4 offices, conference room, work room and 1 handicap restroom. The second floor has 4 offices, 1.5 restrooms and a kitchen. Plenty of parking in the paved lot behind the building (20+ spaces).

Directly on Main St. in downtown Reisterstown. Walking distance to many shops and restaurants and other businesses.

This is the oldest house on MainStreet and was built in 1773 by Jacob Bren. Henry Weist, son-in-law of John Reister the founder of Reisterstown in 1758, lived here. The following renovations were made to the house in 2008; New windows, doors and trim, wood floors were refinished and carpeting replaced, new bathrooms, new kitchen on second floor, upgraded electric service and central air system.

Tenant responsible for all utilities. We're offering for $3400 per month.
